# Sample environment configuration for the thumbnailator project.
#
# Copy this file to `.env` and uncomment + edit the values you want to set:
#
#     cp .env.example .env
#
# All variables below are OPTIONAL. The wrapper works out of the box without
# any of them set; these overrides are useful when you want to share a JAR
# across projects, point at a non-default install path, or test on a host
# that has ImageMagick / GraphicsMagick somewhere other than C:\CFusionExtra\.
#
# CommandBox reads `.env` at project root on `box server start` and
# substitutes ${VAR} references in server*.json with whatever you set here.
# `.env` itself is gitignored, so per-developer values stay local.


# ===========================================================================
# Thumbnailator JAR location
# ===========================================================================
# Default behavior: Application.cfc enumerates `*.jar` files in
# `./lib/thumbnailator/` and adds each to this.javaSettings.loadPaths.
# Override only if you want to share one JAR across multiple projects or
# load it from a system-wide install.
#
# Resolution order:
#   1. THUMBNAILATOR_JAR_PATH if set and the file exists
#   2. THUMBNAILATOR_JAR_DIR  if set and the directory exists
#   3. Bundled ./lib/thumbnailator/  (default fallback)

# Full path to a single .jar file (takes priority):
#THUMBNAILATOR_JAR_PATH=C:\shared\jars\thumbnailator-0.4.21.jar

# Directory containing one or more .jar files (used if _JAR_PATH is unset):
#THUMBNAILATOR_JAR_DIR=C:\shared\jars


# ===========================================================================
# External tool paths (compare.cfm only)
# ===========================================================================
# Used by the benchmarking page at /compare.cfm to locate the ImageMagick
# and GraphicsMagick executables. If unset, compare.cfm checks the default
# install locations under C:\. Set these if you have the
# binaries elsewhere (e.g., a portable install, or a Linux/Mac host).

#IMAGEMAGICK_BIN=C:\ImageMagick\magick.exe
#GRAPHICSMAGICK_BIN=C:\GraphicsMagick\gm.exe


# ===========================================================================
# Notes
# ===========================================================================
# - BoxLang compatibility mode (BOXLANG_COMPAT_MODE) is NOT in this file
#   because it's set per-profile in server-boxlang*.json directly, not via
#   env-var substitution.
# - The serverInfo() helper in tests/_testHelper.cfm and demo.cfm reads
#   BOXLANG_COMPAT_MODE at runtime to label the engine header. That value
#   flows from the server profile's `env` block, not from this .env file.
# - On Windows, do not quote paths in this file. CommandBox passes the raw
#   string through. Quotes will appear as literal characters in the value.
